gives us a Lorentzian.

00:18:47.630 --> 00:18:52.090
So when we ask what is the
rate, Fermi's golden rule's

00:18:52.090 --> 00:18:55.000
rate expression, the
rate for excitation.

00:19:00.950 --> 00:19:04.230
We want to do the Fourier
transform of this correlation

00:19:04.230 --> 00:19:05.850
function.

00:19:05.850 --> 00:19:21.540
And what we obtain is, well,
a Lorentzian which looks

00:19:21.540 --> 00:19:24.320
like the Lorentzian for
spontaneous emission,

00:19:24.320 --> 00:19:30.230
except for that we have
a different width now.

00:19:30.230 --> 00:19:48.720
It's a Lorentzian with a
