00:24:25.680 --> 00:24:28.980
Now we're getting close.

00:24:28.980 --> 00:24:33.720
We assumed diffusive motion.

00:24:33.720 --> 00:24:37.930
We put in the exact expression
for diffusive motion.

00:24:37.930 --> 00:24:41.840
And of course, you also know,
when you describe a line width,

00:24:41.840 --> 00:24:44.310
what happens in the
middle at detuning

00:24:44.310 --> 00:24:48.130
0 is more what happens in
the limit of long times.

00:24:48.130 --> 00:24:54.050
What happens further and further
out happens at shorter times.

00:24:54.050 --> 00:24:56.850
What is the motion of
atoms at short times?

00:25:02.370 --> 00:25:05.850
Before the first collision
happens, it moves straight.

00:25:05.850 --> 00:25:08.950
So the diffusive
propagator which we put in

00:25:08.950 --> 00:25:11.300
is only valid after
the first collision.

00:25:11.300 --> 00:25:14.950
Until the first collision
happens, we have free motion.

00:25:14.950 --> 00:25:19.670
And free motion should give rise
to simple Doppler broadening.

00:25:19.670 --> 00:25:21.380
So until the first
collision happens,

00:25:21.380 --> 00:25:22.990
we should get a little
bit of Doppler broadening.

00:25:22.990 --> 00:25:24.390
But once the
collisions happened,

00:25:24.390 --> 00:25:26.700
we should be very well
within the description

00:25:26.700 --> 00:25:28.740
of the diffusion operator.

00:25:28.740 --> 00:25:31.525
And to address your
concern, actually,

00:25:31.525 --> 00:25:34.340
in the limit of many
sideband, often,

00:25:34.340 --> 00:25:36.860
the envelope of
all those sidebands

00:25:36.860 --> 00:25:38.960
is actually determined
by the Doppler profile.

00:25:38.960 --> 00:25:42.470
There is a limit, if you have
a large modulation index,

00:25:42.470 --> 00:25:45.890
that you have many sidebands.

00:25:45.890 --> 00:25:47.800
And in some
semi-classical limit,

00:25:47.800 --> 00:25:51.310
the sidebands have an envelope
which is the Doppler profile.

00:25:51.310 --> 00:25:54.100
So now I think the
two pictures agree.

00:25:54.100 --> 00:26:02.560
If we had used a propagator
which would interpolate

00:26:02.560 --> 00:26:05.470
between the first moment where
the particle moves straight,

00:26:05.470 --> 00:26:09.030
and then diffusion, we would
have gotten little pedestals

00:26:09.030 --> 00:26:10.400
here.

00:26:10.400 --> 00:26:14.870
And so that sort of tells us
that the smeared outside bands,

00:26:14.870 --> 00:26:18.460
yes, strictly speaking, they
are linked to harmonic motion.

00:26:18.460 --> 00:26:19.954
But they are sort
of the leftover

00:26:19.954 --> 00:26:22.120
of the motional effect,
which is the Doppler effect.

00:26:25.410 --> 00:26:25.910
OK.

00:26:30.401 --> 00:26:30.900
Good.

00:26:30.900 --> 00:26:35.600
So we have the
correct answer here.

00:26:35.600 --> 00:26:46.130
And here, it is the model
neglects ballistic motion

00:26:46.130 --> 00:26:51.465
until the first collision.

