01:14:30.480 --> 01:14:31.930
And this is the following.

01:14:31.930 --> 01:14:34.880
We do first-order
perturbation theory,

01:14:34.880 --> 01:14:38.210
which takes us in the first
step to the intermediate state.

01:14:38.210 --> 01:14:42.290
And you have seen this
expression many, many times.

01:14:42.290 --> 01:14:46.860
The only thing is in addition to
what we had for one laser beam,

01:14:46.860 --> 01:14:50.158
we have to add a second
possibility, which

01:14:50.158 --> 01:14:51.324
comes from the second field.

01:14:55.040 --> 01:14:57.630
And now we are at the
intermediate step.

01:14:57.630 --> 01:15:00.900
And we want to take the second
step to the final state.

01:15:00.900 --> 01:15:03.940
So what we are now doing is we
are writing down Schrodinger's

01:15:03.940 --> 01:15:06.410
equation, derivative
of the wave function

01:15:06.410 --> 01:15:09.410
is Hamiltonian times
the wave function.

01:15:09.410 --> 01:15:11.450
And we are especially
interested in how

01:15:11.450 --> 01:15:16.930
do we accumulate probability or
amplitude in the final state.

01:15:16.930 --> 01:15:21.200
But what we are doing is
on the right-hand side,

01:15:21.200 --> 01:15:23.090
because we can't start
in the ground state,

01:15:23.090 --> 01:15:24.870
we've gone to the
intermediate state,

01:15:24.870 --> 01:15:28.040
we are now plugging in
the previous result,

01:15:28.040 --> 01:15:31.530
the first-order result for
the intermediate state.

01:15:31.530 --> 01:15:34.212
So therefore, by using
second-order perturbation

01:15:34.212 --> 01:15:36.420
theory, we want the second-order
perturbation theory,

01:15:36.420 --> 01:15:39.660
so we integrate this equation
with respect to time.

01:15:39.660 --> 01:15:43.450
But on the right side, we
use our first-order result,

01:15:43.450 --> 01:15:46.900
which we had derived earlier.

01:15:46.900 --> 01:15:49.180
And then we just write
down the integral.

01:15:49.180 --> 01:15:51.780
Everything is just
exponential function.

01:15:51.780 --> 01:15:53.910
And we get the result here.

01:15:53.910 --> 01:16:04.770
So now with two steps, we
